name: ds-777-spatial-location-of-gages-with-total-flow-and-estimated-base-flow-organized-by-seasonal-
notes: Baseflow is the portion of streamflow derived from groundwater flow. It is an important component of the groundwater budget, and can be estimated using known total streamflow at given points through time. Daily streamflow data was collected from 91 streamflow gaging stations across the northern High Plains Groundwater Availability Study (NHPGAS) area from the National Water Information System (NWIS) and the Nebraska Department of Natural Resources Stream Gaging Data Bank. The data from each site was processed using the BFI program, version 4.15 (Wahl and Wahl, 2007) to determine the baseflow component of total streamflow at each site. The average daily baseflow was computed for the months of April and October, spanning the development period model (1940-2009). The resulting baseflow values were applied as calibration targets to corresponding stress periods.

extras.value: ["Use Constraints: This dataset was compiled to provide the computed baseflow values used as calibration targets in the northern High Plains groundwater-flow model. It also provides the estimated total streamflow compiled from multiple agencies, and the computed baseflow to total streamflow ratio. It is only intended to illustrate these results.", "Access Constraints: None"]
